You are starting a new `Thread` per `SieveWorker`. You should either use `SieveWorker` which is a `Thread`

     workers[i] = new SieveWorker(start, end, i);
     workers[i].start();

Or make `SieveWorker` extend Runnable and create a `Thread` with that worker as the task, and store each thread in another array `Thread[] threads = new Thread[num_of_threads];`. Afterwards join on the `threads[]` not `workers[]`.

     workers[i] = new SieveWorker(start, end, i);
     threads[i] = new Thread(workers[i]);
     threads[i].start();

